## **Description**
The **MultiReplace **operator allows to perform multiple substitutions within an input string, based on the configuration settings.

## **Input**
**Input**

**Data type**

**Description**

**in0**

String

The string in which you want to apply the partial replacements

## **Output**
**Output**

**Data type**

**Description**

**out0**

String

The resulting string, based on the configuration settings

## **![](data:image/png;base64,)****Settings**
- In the **Strings **section, click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) to add a string to the list.

- Enter the value that you want to search for in the **Match **field, and the value that you want to replace it with in the **Replace **column.

> Important

If multiple substitutions are specified, the operator will apply them in the order in which they appear.

- Click **Apply **to confirm.

> Tip

To modify a string, click on its name to edit it.

To remove a string from the list, move your mouse over it and click ![](data:image/png;base64,) 	in the **Action **column; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## **Special cases**
In special cases, the operator behaves as follows:

**Case**

**Behavior**

**NULL input (no input)**

The operator returns an empty string.

**Input with NULL value**

The operator returns an empty string.
